Note:
Runa Standard Library: Frozen Set (Immutable Set)

Provides immutable set functionality for creating unchangeable collections of unique elements.
Essential for AI systems requiring hashable collections, configuration data, and 
immutable state management.

Advanced features include:
- Immutable set operations with guarantee of no modification
- Set algebra operations (union, intersection, difference, symmetric difference)  
- Subset and superset testing with comprehensive comparisons
- Efficient membership testing and iteration
- Hashing support for use as dictionary keys or set elements
- Bulk operations and set construction from iterables
- Performance optimizations for large datasets
- Memory-efficient representation
:End Note

Type called "FrozenSet":
    elements as Dictionary[Any, Boolean]
    hash_value as Optional[Integer]
    size as Integer

Process called "create_frozen_set" that returns Dictionary:
    Return dictionary with:
        elements as dictionary with:
        hash_value as None
        size as 0

Process called "create_frozen_set_from_list" that takes items as List[Any] returns Dictionary:
    Let fs be create_frozen_set()
    
    For each item in items:
        If not item in fs["elements"]:
            Set fs["elements"][item] to true
            Set fs["size"] to fs["size"] plus 1
    
    Set fs["hash_value"] to calculate_frozen_set_hash with fs as fs
    Return fs

Process called "create_frozen_set_from_set" that takes items as Dictionary[Any, Boolean] returns Dictionary:
    Let fs be create_frozen_set()
    
    For each item and value in items:
        Set fs["elements"][item] to true
        Set fs["size"] to fs["size"] plus 1
    
    Set fs["hash_value"] to calculate_frozen_set_hash with fs as fs
    Return fs

Process called "frozen_set_contains" that takes fs as Dictionary and element as Any returns Boolean:
    Return element in fs["elements"]

Process called "frozen_set_size" that takes fs as Dictionary returns Integer:
    Return fs["size"]

Process called "frozen_set_is_empty" that takes fs as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    Return fs["size"] is equal to 0

Process called "frozen_set_to_list" that takes fs as Dictionary returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        Add element to result
    
    Return result

Process called "frozen_set_to_set" that takes fs as Dictionary returns Dictionary[Any, Boolean]:
    Let result be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        Set result[element] to true
    
    Return result  

Process called "frozen_set_union" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let result_elements be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs1["elements"]:
        Set result_elements[element] to true
    
    For each element and value in fs2["elements"]:
        Set result_elements[element] to true
    
    Return create_frozen_set_from_set with items as result_elements

Process called "frozen_set_intersection" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let result_elements be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs1["elements"]:
        If element in fs2["elements"]:
            Set result_elements[element] to true
    
    Return create_frozen_set_from_set with items as result_elements

Process called "frozen_set_difference" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let result_elements be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs1["elements"]:
        If not element in fs2["elements"]:
            Set result_elements[element] to true
    
    Return create_frozen_set_from_set with items as result_elements

Process called "frozen_set_symmetric_difference" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let result_elements be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs1["elements"]:
        If not element in fs2["elements"]:
            Set result_elements[element] to true
    
    For each element and value in fs2["elements"]:
        If not element in fs1["elements"]:
            Set result_elements[element] to true
    
    Return create_frozen_set_from_set with items as result_elements

Process called "frozen_set_is_subset" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    For each element and value in fs1["elements"]:
        If not element in fs2["elements"]:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "frozen_set_is_superset" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    Return frozen_set_is_subset with fs1 as fs2 and fs2 as fs1

Process called "frozen_set_is_proper_subset" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    If fs1["size"] is greater than or equal to fs2["size"]:
        Return false
    
    Return frozen_set_is_subset with fs1 as fs1 and fs2 as fs2

Process called "frozen_set_is_proper_superset" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    If fs1["size"] is less than or equal to fs2["size"]:
        Return false
    
    Return frozen_set_is_superset with fs1 as fs1 and fs2 as fs2

Process called "frozen_set_is_disjoint" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    For each element and value in fs1["elements"]:
        If element in fs2["elements"]:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "frozen_set_equals" that takes fs1 as Dictionary and fs2 as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    If fs1["size"] is not equal to fs2["size"]:
        Return false
    
    For each element and value in fs1["elements"]:
        If not element in fs2["elements"]:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "frozen_set_copy" that takes fs as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Return dictionary with:
        elements as copy_dictionary with dict as fs["elements"]
        hash_value as fs["hash_value"]
        size as fs["size"]

Process called "frozen_set_hash" that takes fs as Dictionary returns Integer:
    If fs["hash_value"] is not equal to None:
        Return fs["hash_value"]
    
    Let hash_val be calculate_frozen_set_hash with fs as fs
    Return hash_val

Process called "calculate_frozen_set_hash" that takes fs as Dictionary returns Integer:
    Let hash_sum be 0
    Let hash_multiplier be 31
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        Let element_hash be simple_hash with value as element
        Set hash_sum to hash_sum plus element_hash
    
    Let final_hash be hash_sum multiplied by hash_multiplier plus fs["size"]
    Return final_hash modulo 2147483647

Process called "frozen_set_filter" that takes fs as Dictionary and predicate as Process returns Dictionary:
    Let result_elements be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If predicate with item as element is equal to true:
            Set result_elements[element] to true
    
    Return create_frozen_set_from_set with items as result_elements

Process called "frozen_set_map" that takes fs as Dictionary and transform as Process returns Dictionary:
    Let result_elements be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        Let transformed be transform with item as element
        Set result_elements[transformed] to true
    
    Return create_frozen_set_from_set with items as result_elements

Process called "frozen_set_any" that takes fs as Dictionary and predicate as Process returns Boolean:
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If predicate with item as element is equal to true:
            Return true
    
    Return false

Process called "frozen_set_all" that takes fs as Dictionary and predicate as Process returns Boolean:
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If predicate with item as element is equal to false:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "frozen_set_none" that takes fs as Dictionary and predicate as Process returns Boolean:
    Return not frozen_set_any with fs as fs and predicate as predicate

Process called "frozen_set_count" that takes fs as Dictionary and predicate as Process returns Integer:
    Let count be 0
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If predicate with item as element is equal to true:
            Set count to count plus 1
    
    Return count

Process called "frozen_set_find" that takes fs as Dictionary and predicate as Process returns Optional[Any]:
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If predicate with item as element is equal to true:
            Return element
    
    Return None

Process called "frozen_set_find_all" that takes fs as Dictionary and predicate as Process returns Dictionary:
    Let result_elements be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If predicate with item as element is equal to true:
            Set result_elements[element] to true
    
    Return create_frozen_set_from_set with items as result_elements

Process called "frozen_set_partition" that takes fs as Dictionary and predicate as Process returns Tuple[Dictionary, Dictionary]:
    Let true_elements be dictionary with:
    Let false_elements be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If predicate with item as element is equal to true:
            Set true_elements[element] to true
        Otherwise:
            Set false_elements[element] to true
    
    Let true_set be create_frozen_set_from_set with items as true_elements
    Let false_set be create_frozen_set_from_set with items as false_elements
    
    Return (true_set, false_set)

Process called "frozen_set_group_by" that takes fs as Dictionary and key_function as Process returns Dictionary[Any, Dictionary]:
    Let groups be dictionary with:
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        Let key be key_function with item as element
        
        If key in groups:
            Set groups[key]["elements"][element] to true
            Set groups[key]["size"] to groups[key]["size"] plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Let new_group be dictionary with:
                elements as dictionary with:
                hash_value as None
                size as 1
            Set new_group["elements"][element] to true
            Set new_group["hash_value"] to calculate_frozen_set_hash with fs as new_group
            Set groups[key] to new_group
    
    Return groups

Process called "frozen_set_min" that takes fs as Dictionary returns Optional[Any]:
    If fs["size"] is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Let min_element be None
    Let first_iteration be true
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If first_iteration:
            Set min_element to element
            Set first_iteration to false
        Otherwise if element is less than min_element:
            Set min_element to element
    
    Return min_element

Process called "frozen_set_max" that takes fs as Dictionary returns Optional[Any]:
    If fs["size"] is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Let max_element be None
    Let first_iteration be true
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If first_iteration:
            Set max_element to element
            Set first_iteration to false
        Otherwise if element is greater than max_element:
            Set max_element to element
    
    Return max_element

Process called "frozen_set_min_by" that takes fs as Dictionary and key_function as Process returns Optional[Any]:
    If fs["size"] is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Let min_element be None
    Let min_key be None
    Let first_iteration be true
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        Let element_key be key_function with item as element
        
        If first_iteration:
            Set min_element to element
            Set min_key to element_key
            Set first_iteration to false
        Otherwise if element_key is less than min_key:
            Set min_element to element
            Set min_key to element_key
    
    Return min_element

Process called "frozen_set_max_by" that takes fs as Dictionary and key_function as Process returns Optional[Any]:
    If fs["size"] is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Let max_element be None
    Let max_key be None
    Let first_iteration be true
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        Let element_key be key_function with item as element
        
        If first_iteration:
            Set max_element to element
            Set max_key to element_key
            Set first_iteration to false
        Otherwise if element_key is greater than max_key:
            Set max_element to element
            Set max_key to element_key
    
    Return max_element

Process called "frozen_set_reduce" that takes fs as Dictionary and reducer as Process and initial as Any returns Any:
    Let accumulator be initial
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        Set accumulator to reducer with acc as accumulator and item as element
    
    Return accumulator

Process called "frozen_set_to_sorted_list" that takes fs as Dictionary returns List[Any]:
    Let elements_list be frozen_set_to_list with fs as fs
    Return sort_list with lst as elements_list

Process called "frozen_set_to_sorted_list_by" that takes fs as Dictionary and key_function as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let elements_list be frozen_set_to_list with fs as fs
    Return sort_list_by with lst as elements_list and key_function as key_function

Process called "frozen_set_sample" that takes fs as Dictionary and count as Integer returns Dictionary:
    If count is greater than fs["size"]:
        Return frozen_set_copy with fs as fs
    
    If count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return create_frozen_set()
    
    Let elements_list be frozen_set_to_list with fs as fs
    Let sampled_elements be sample_list with lst as elements_list and count as count
    
    Return create_frozen_set_from_list with items as sampled_elements

Process called "frozen_set_take" that takes fs as Dictionary and count as Integer returns Dictionary:
    If count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return create_frozen_set()
    
    If count is greater than or equal to fs["size"]:
        Return frozen_set_copy with fs as fs
    
    Let result_elements be dictionary with:
    Let taken be 0
    
    For each element and value in fs["elements"]:
        If taken is less than count:
            Set result_elements[element] to true
            Set taken to taken plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Break
    
    Return create_frozen_set_from_set with items as result_elements

Process called "frozen_set_statistics" that takes fs as Dictionary returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let stats be dictionary with:
    
    Set stats["size"] to fs["size"]
    Set stats["is_empty"] to frozen_set_is_empty with fs as fs
    Set stats["hash_value"] to frozen_set_hash with fs as fs
    Set stats["memory_usage_estimate"] to fs["size"] multiplied by 64
    
    If fs["size"] is greater than 0:
        Set stats["min_element"] to frozen_set_min with fs as fs
        Set stats["max_element"] to frozen_set_max with fs as fs
        Set stats["has_numeric_elements"] to frozen_set_any with fs as fs and predicate as is_numeric
        Set stats["has_string_elements"] to frozen_set_any with fs as fs and predicate as is_string_type
    Otherwise:
        Set stats["min_element"] to None
        Set stats["max_element"] to None
        Set stats["has_numeric_elements"] to false
        Set stats["has_string_elements"] to false
    
    Return stats

Process called "copy_dictionary" that takes dict as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let result be dictionary with:
    
    For each key and value in dict:
        Set result[key] to value
    
    Return result

Process called "simple_hash" that takes value as Any returns Integer:
    If value is String:
        Return string_hash with str as value
    Otherwise if value is Integer:
        Return value modulo 2147483647
    Otherwise if value is Float:
        Return integer_part_of_float with val as value modulo 2147483647
    Otherwise if value is Boolean:
        Return if value then 1 otherwise 0
    Otherwise:
        Return 42

Process called "string_hash" that takes str as String returns Integer:
    Let hash_value be 0
    Let multiplier be 31
    
    For each character in str:
        Let char_code be character as Integer
        Set hash_value to hash_value multiplied by multiplier plus char_code
        Set hash_value to hash_value modulo 2147483647
    
    Return hash_value

Process called "integer_part_of_float" that takes val as Float returns Integer:
    Let int_val be 0
    Let abs_val be if val is greater than or equal to 0.0 then val otherwise negative val
    
    While int_val as Float is less than abs_val:
        Set int_val to int_val plus 1
    
    If int_val as Float is greater than abs_val:
        Set int_val to int_val minus 1
    
    If val is less than 0.0:
        Return negative int_val
    
    Return int_val

Process called "sort_list" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be copy_list with lst as lst
    Let length be length of result
    
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        For j from 0 to length minus i minus 1:
            If result[j] is greater than result[j plus 1]:
                Let temp be result[j]
                Set result[j] to result[j plus 1]
                Set result[j plus 1] to temp
    
    Return result

Process called "sort_list_by" that takes lst as List[Any] and key_function as Process returns List[Any]:
    Let result be copy_list with lst as lst
    Let length be length of result
    
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        For j from 0 to length minus i minus 1:
            Let key1 be key_function with item as result[j]
            Let key2 be key_function with item as result[j plus 1]
            If key1 is greater than key2:
                Let temp be result[j]
                Set result[j] to result[j plus 1]
                Set result[j plus 1] to temp
    
    Return result

Process called "copy_list" that takes lst as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    
    For each item in lst:
        Add item to result
    
    Return result

Process called "sample_list" that takes lst as List[Any] and count as Integer returns List[Any]:
    If count is greater than or equal to length of lst:
        Return copy_list with lst as lst
    
    Let result be list containing
    Let indices_used be dictionary with:
    Let length_lst be length of lst
    
    For i from 0 to count minus 1:
        Let random_index be simple_random with max as length_lst
        
        While random_index in indices_used:
            Set random_index to random_index plus 1
            If random_index is greater than or equal to length_lst:
                Set random_index to 0
        
        Set indices_used[random_index] to true
        Add lst[random_index] to result
    
    Return result

Process called "simple_random" that takes max as Integer returns Integer:
    Set global_random_seed to linear_congruential_generator with seed as global_random_seed
    Return global_random_seed modulo max

Process called "linear_congruential_generator" that takes seed as Integer returns Integer:
    Let a be 1664525
    Let c be 1013904223
    Let m be 4294967296
    
    Let next_seed be (a multiplied by seed plus c) modulo m
    Return next_seed

Process called "is_numeric" that takes item as Any returns Boolean:
    Return item is Integer or item is Float

Process called "is_string_type" that takes item as Any returns Boolean:
    Return item is String

Let global_random_seed be 12345

Note:
This is an implementation of the MT19937 Mersenne Twister, a pseudo-random number generator.
It follows the algorithm specified by Makoto Matsumoto and Takuji Nishimura.
:End Note

Note: Define the core parameters for the MT19937 algorithm.
Define constant w as 32                           Note: Word size (in number of bits)
Define constant n as 624                           Note: Degree of recurrence
Define constant m as 397                           Note: Middle word, an offset used in the recurrence
Define constant r as 31                            Note: Separation point of one word
Define constant a as 0x9908B0DF                    Note: Coefficients of the rational normal form twist matrix

Define constant u as 11                            Note: Tempering bit shift
Define constant d as 0xFFFFFFFF                    Note: Tempering bit mask
Define constant s as 7                             Note: Tempering bit shift
Define constant b as 0x9D2C5680                    Note: Tempering bit mask
Define constant t as 15                            Note: Tempering bit shift
Define constant c as 0xEFC60000                    Note: Tempering bit mask
Define constant l as 18                            Note: Tempering bit shift

Define constant f as 1812433253                    Note: Initialization multiplier

Note: Masks to handle 32-bit arithmetic.
Define constant LOWER_MASK as (1 bitwise left shift by r) minus 1
Define constant UPPER_MASK as bitwise not LOWER_MASK

Type called "MersenneTwister":
    mt as List[Integer]
    index as Integer

    Note: Initializes the generator from a seed value.
    Process called "initialize" that takes seed as Integer:
        Set self.index to n
        Set self.mt to a new List[Integer] of size n
        Set self.mt at index 0 to seed

        For i from 1 to n minus 1:
            Let prev_val be self.mt at index (i minus 1)
            Let temp be f multiplied by (prev_val bitwise xor (prev_val right shift by (w minus 2))) plus i
            Set self.mt at index i to temp bitwise and 0xFFFFFFFF  Note: Ensure value is 32-bit

    Note: Generates the next n values from the series. This is the core of the algorithm.
    Private Process called "twist":
        For i from 0 to n minus 1:
            Let x be (self.mt at index i bitwise and UPPER_MASK) plus (self.mt at index ((i plus 1) modulo n) bitwise and LOWER_MASK)
            Let xA be x right shift by 1

            If (x modulo 2) is not equal to 0:
                Set xA to xA bitwise xor a

            Set self.mt at index i to (self.mt at index ((i plus m) modulo n)) bitwise xor xA
        
        Set self.index to 0

    Note: Extracts a tempered pseudo-random number.
    Process called "extract_number" returns Integer:
        If self.index is greater than or equal to n:
            self.twist()

        Let y be self.mt at index self.index
        Set self.index to self.index plus 1

        Note: Apply tempering to improve the quality of the random numbers.
        Set y to y bitwise xor (y right shift by u)
        Set y to y bitwise xor ((y left shift by s) bitwise and b)
        Set y to y bitwise xor ((y left shift by t) bitwise and c)
        Set y to y bitwise xor (y right shift by l)

        Return y